## History

This rule was written 2026-05-23 in direct response to:

> "I need this fucking prevented. You've made so many mistakes in our
> conversation. I need you to make a rule for this mvp plan that ties
> in everything I've told you to do for this convo." — user

Specific incidents captured above. If a future agent (or future me)
is tempted to ship a docs-only "X is SHIPPED" PR while X's code sits
on a local branch, STOP and re-read this rule.

§9 (one-agent-per-Phase prompt-writing) was added 2026-05-23 in
response to:

> "Remember that each phase has it's own dedicated agent for all of
> it's chunks, might want to put that reminder in the rules for when
> writing the new chunks, it'll probably save tokens when writing
> the prompts" — user

The triggering observation: Chunk 2.2's hand-off prompt re-listed
every CARFAX service file the Phase 2 agent had already built or
read during Chunk 2.1, re-stated the Phase 2 sub-bullet block, and
opened with "You are starting a fresh Cursor chat" — all bloat that
the in-context agent ignores at best and trips on at worst. The
rule codifies the pattern so the next mid-Phase chunk (2.3, 3.2,
etc.) opens lean.
